chunk_content: Identify the level of engagement in PT activities for each POCT site by choosing one of the following: • Performs this test but does not participate in PT (see definition of ‘PT participation’ below). 183 • Performs this test and participates in PT. Sum the number of specimens received for testing at all POCT sites within a testing category. See H definition for “specimens received for testing.” E A DEFINITIONS (LABORATORY-BASED TESTING SITES): L T H Laboratory: A. Having dedicated physical laboratory infrastructure S Y B. Having dedicated trained laboratory professionals performing testing S C. Conducting laboratory testing in one or more of the following areas: T a. Diagnosis of HIV infection with rapid test kits, EIA, WB, or other molecular methods E M b. Infant Virologic Testing / Early Infant Diagnosis (IVT/EID) S c. HIV viral load d. TB diagnostics: molecular WHO-recommended diagnostic (mWRD), LF-LAM, AFB, or culture e. CD4 f.
